// frame_moving.su — an ANIMATABLE glow, rendered whole-frame in one substrate op.
//
// Generalizes frame_whole.su: the glow is centred at a movable x-position `cx`
// instead of fixed at the origin, so sweeping `cx` across frames animates the glow
// sliding horizontally. Still one substrate op per frame, still the whole frame as
// one buffer vector (Emma's model). The host reshapes + paints each frame.
//
//   frame_at(x, y, ones, cx) = ones - hadamard(x - cx, x - cx) - hadamard(y, y)
//                            = 1 - (x - cx)^2 - y^2
//
// `x`, `y`, `ones`, `cx` are length-(N*N) coordinate buffers the orchestrator builds;
// `cx` is the per-frame centre broadcast to every pixel (it's what the host advances
// to animate). `hadamard` is the elementwise/buffer product (one op over all pixels).
function vector frame_at(vector x, vector y, vector ones, vector cx) {
    vector dx = x - cx;
    return ones - hadamard(dx, dx) - hadamard(y, y);
}

// Self-contained sanity entry: glow at the origin, centre pixel -> 1 - 0 - 0 = 1.
function vector main() {
    return frame_at(make_real(0.0), make_real(0.0), make_real(1.0), make_real(0.0));
}
